{"word":"ἐράω","slug":"ἐράω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐράω1</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to love, to be in love with</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>ἐρᾶν ἔρωτα</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ἐρῶν</el> <i>a lover</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>ἡ ἐρωμένη</el> <i>the beloved one</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of things, <i>to love</i> or <i>desire passionately</i>, <el>τυραννίδος</el> <b><a href='S:Archilochus Lyricus'>Archil.</a></b>; <el>μάχης</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; and <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to desire</i> to do, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div> <hr/> <el><b>ἐράω2</b></el> <p/><i>to pour out, vomit forth</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/>"}]}